1
00:00:08,250 --> 00:00:11,750
<i>We were at our happiest,</i>

2
00:00:11,750 --> 00:00:15,080
<i>and she dropped us into the pits of misery.</i>

3
00:00:23,580 --> 00:00:26,470
How is Sayaka feeling?

4
00:00:27,850 --> 00:00:30,260
She's recovering.

5
00:00:30,260 --> 00:00:32,370
I see.

6
00:00:32,370 --> 00:00:38,480
I'm sorry my girl keeps causing you trouble.

7
00:00:38,480 --> 00:00:40,220
No worries.

8
00:00:40,930 --> 00:00:43,460
<i>Only one suspect remains.</i>

9
00:00:43,460 --> 00:00:48,680
<i>Kaori Wakamatsu - Sayaka's mother.</i>

10
00:00:57,820 --> 00:00:59,500
This is delicious!

11
00:00:59,500 --> 00:01:01,050
I'm glad to hear it.

12
00:01:01,050 --> 00:01:02,710
Thank you again, Kazuomi.

13
00:01:02,710 --> 00:01:08,800
Holding another ceremony
is nothing short of a dream.

14
00:01:08,800 --> 00:01:12,510
I knew you were a reliable man.

15
00:01:13,280 --> 00:01:19,120
I just want our wedding
to be a happy memory for Sayaka.

16
00:01:19,120 --> 00:01:20,810
Is that so?

17
00:01:21,560 --> 00:01:28,540
I was so frustrated the ceremony ended
the way it did.

18
00:01:28,540 --> 00:01:34,390
A wedding is once in a lifetime.
I wouldn't want to have regrets.

19
00:01:36,410 --> 00:01:41,990
<i>She's been spearheading this ceremony
as if it were her very own.</i>

20
00:01:42,770 --> 00:01:47,710
<i>She chose the venue, Sayaka's dress, and...</i>

21
00:01:47,710 --> 00:01:52,210
I would like my daughter to play the violin
after her vows.

22
00:01:52,210 --> 00:01:53,340
What?

23
00:01:53,340 --> 00:01:57,720
Performing in a pristine dress...
Doesn't that sound lovely?

24
00:01:57,720 --> 00:01:58,850
Yes.

25
00:01:58,850 --> 00:02:01,640
I'm sure the crowd would love that.

26
00:02:01,640 --> 00:02:08,830
<i>She pushed Sayaka to perform,
and even chose the piece.</i>

27
00:02:08,830 --> 00:02:13,200
<i>She was likely aware
of our catering menu as well.</i>

28
00:02:16,190 --> 00:02:21,840
<i>Which would mean she knew
of the blue champagne.</i>

29
00:02:21,840 --> 00:02:25,990
Kazuomi, would you be a dear
and hand this to Sayaka for me?

30
00:02:27,760 --> 00:02:28,700
[J.S. Bach]

31
00:02:28,700 --> 00:02:30,560
And this is?

32
00:02:30,560 --> 00:02:32,210
A score, of course.

33
00:02:32,210 --> 00:02:34,740
It's for the upcoming ceremony.

34
00:02:34,740 --> 00:02:37,410
We can't have her perform the same piece.

35
00:02:37,410 --> 00:02:41,770
This is a concerto for two, composed by Bach.

36
00:02:41,770 --> 00:02:43,420
You're having her perform, again?

37
00:02:43,420 --> 00:02:48,270
Yes! Sayaka and I will duet this time.

38
00:02:48,270 --> 00:02:49,280
But...

39
00:02:49,280 --> 00:02:53,460
Tell her to practice hard, alright?

40
00:02:54,850 --> 00:02:56,550
Mother, I don't think -

41
00:02:56,550 --> 00:02:58,770
My, would you look at the time?

42
00:02:58,770 --> 00:03:02,020
I must be heading to the clinic.

43
00:03:03,980 --> 00:03:05,830
Clinic?

44
00:03:05,830 --> 00:03:09,500
Yes. I have to pick up
my prescribed medication.

45
00:03:11,060 --> 00:03:12,410
Medication?

46
00:03:12,410 --> 00:03:16,790
<i>There is a medicine
that turns water blue when dissolved.</i>

47
00:03:16,790 --> 00:03:18,700
<i>It's a type of sleeping pill.</i>

48
00:03:20,350 --> 00:03:22,450
What sort of medication, if I may ask?

49
00:03:24,040 --> 00:03:27,710
Oh, it's just my usual prescription.

50
00:03:39,570 --> 00:03:41,670
I'll be headed this way.

51
00:03:41,670 --> 00:03:43,980
Take care.

52
00:04:09,070 --> 00:04:11,730
The "usual prescription", is it?

53
00:04:11,730 --> 00:04:13,790
<i>Yeah. She didn't specify what it was for.</i>

54
00:04:13,790 --> 00:04:15,810
Suspicious, right?

55
00:04:15,810 --> 00:04:18,720
Either way, I'll continue tailing her.

56
00:04:18,720 --> 00:04:20,060
<i>Careful not to get caught.</i>

57
00:04:20,060 --> 00:04:22,150
Yeah, yeah.

58
00:04:25,880 --> 00:04:28,470
Close call.

59
00:04:35,960 --> 00:04:40,270
Honestly, I've had my suspicions about her.

60
00:04:40,270 --> 00:04:44,400
Given how Sayaka's mother is,
it stemmed from issues at home.

61
00:04:44,400 --> 00:04:48,040
You know how her mother is, right?

62
00:04:48,740 --> 00:04:53,580
Sayaka was always overly conscious
of her mother.

63
00:04:54,140 --> 00:04:57,040
It's like she was her mother's puppet.

64
00:04:57,040 --> 00:05:00,040
To force an activity onto her child,

65
00:05:00,040 --> 00:05:03,170
<i>and exhibit controlling tendencies...</i>

66
00:05:03,170 --> 00:05:06,800
She's the very definition of a toxic parent.

67
00:05:07,500 --> 00:05:10,920
That doesn't mean she had no love for Sayaka.

68
00:05:10,920 --> 00:05:16,720
We'll never know
unless we press her about it ourselves.

69
00:05:38,630 --> 00:05:39,870
[Ikebashi Mental Health Clinic]

70
00:05:39,870 --> 00:05:43,420
"Mental Health Clinic".

71
00:05:44,280 --> 00:05:47,270
It seems she's seeing a psychiatrist.

72
00:05:47,270 --> 00:05:49,630
A psychiatrist?

73
00:05:49,630 --> 00:05:52,040
<i>I'll head in, and continue observing her.</i>

74
00:05:52,040 --> 00:05:54,020
<i>I'll call back with any reports.</i>

75
00:06:09,020 --> 00:06:10,460
I'm home.

76
00:06:10,460 --> 00:06:12,550
Welcome back.

77
00:06:14,420 --> 00:06:17,080
I'm sorry I couldn't join you two today.

78
00:06:17,080 --> 00:06:19,510
No need to apologize.

79
00:06:19,510 --> 00:06:22,030
You should still be resting anyway.

80
00:06:23,370 --> 00:06:26,240
What did my mother say?

81
00:06:29,390 --> 00:06:32,010
She was worried about you.

82
00:06:33,460 --> 00:06:35,020
I see.

83
00:06:37,490 --> 00:06:40,750
What's that?

84
00:06:42,180 --> 00:06:44,520
This? It's nothing.

85
00:06:46,520 --> 00:06:52,000
Your mother sounded excited
for the second ceremony.

86
00:06:53,720 --> 00:06:55,490
- Really?
- Yeah.

87
00:06:58,880 --> 00:07:02,520
Thank you, Kazu.

88
00:07:05,800 --> 00:07:07,770
I'm looking forward to it, too.

89
00:07:10,250 --> 00:07:13,050
Mrs. Wakamatsu. Mrs. Kaori Wakamatsu.

90
00:07:13,050 --> 00:07:14,300
Here.

91
00:07:14,300 --> 00:07:15,940
Please state your full name.

92
00:07:15,940 --> 00:07:17,580
Kaori Wakamatsu.

93
00:07:17,580 --> 00:07:20,330
And your primary psychiatrist
is Dr. Sato, correct?

94
00:07:20,330 --> 00:07:23,980
- Yes.
- Dr. Sato has prescribed you two medications.

95
00:07:51,040 --> 00:07:56,250
She was given a medication to take
after meals, and before bed.

96
00:07:56,250 --> 00:07:58,440
Before bed.

97
00:07:58,440 --> 00:08:00,040
Does this mean...

98
00:08:00,040 --> 00:08:03,490
<i>Yes. She was likely given sleeping pills.</i>

99
00:08:05,240 --> 00:08:07,290
That's it.

100
00:08:07,290 --> 00:08:09,420
Shall we confirm the facts ourselves?

101
00:08:17,550 --> 00:08:19,780
We're finally going head-to-head
with the culprit.

102
00:08:19,780 --> 00:08:23,760
We can't afford to make mistakes here.
[Wakamatsu]

103
00:08:23,760 --> 00:08:26,980
Let's not get hasty, alright?

104
00:08:26,980 --> 00:08:30,440
[Wakamatsu]

105
00:08:31,700 --> 00:08:33,260
<i>Yes?</i>

106
00:08:33,260 --> 00:08:34,330
This is Hayashida.

107
00:08:34,330 --> 00:08:37,090
<i>Welcome! I'll open the gates for you.</i>

108
00:08:49,990 --> 00:08:52,210
You're quite early.

109
00:08:52,210 --> 00:08:54,750
We apologize for visiting
on such short notice.

110
00:08:58,760 --> 00:09:03,150
He'll be creating the slideshow
for our ceremony.

111
00:09:03,150 --> 00:09:06,050
I see. Well, I have plenty of photos to share.

112
00:09:06,050 --> 00:09:07,620
I hope you find whatever you need.

113
00:09:07,620 --> 00:09:08,620
Thank you.

114
00:09:08,620 --> 00:09:14,410
If I knew, I would have given you
the pictures over lunch, Kazuomi.

115
00:09:14,410 --> 00:09:18,840
In any case, come on in.
Sorry for the mess.

116
00:09:18,840 --> 00:09:20,440
Thank you for having us.

117
00:09:20,440 --> 00:09:22,230
Thank you.

118
00:09:26,950 --> 00:09:28,620
That's her bag.

119
00:09:29,350 --> 00:09:30,460
I'll go grab it now.

120
00:09:30,460 --> 00:09:32,670
No, she's headed our way!

121
00:09:32,670 --> 00:09:34,880
It's fine, I've got this.

122
00:09:36,830 --> 00:09:38,320
Everything alright?

123
00:09:38,320 --> 00:09:40,680
Yes, fine.

124
00:09:40,680 --> 00:09:42,600
Here you go.

125
00:09:42,600 --> 00:09:44,190
Thank you.

126
00:10:02,160 --> 00:10:04,710
We lost our chance.

127
00:10:04,710 --> 00:10:10,940
Let's plan to get her to open up
through conversation.

128
00:10:10,940 --> 00:10:14,310
If only I could directly ask
if those were sleeping pills.

129
00:10:14,310 --> 00:10:18,470
Don't get pushy. She'll start to suspect us.

130
00:10:22,970 --> 00:10:24,760
Here are the albums.

131
00:10:24,760 --> 00:10:26,670
Thank you.

132
00:10:34,910 --> 00:10:37,120
She's adorable.

133
00:10:37,120 --> 00:10:39,410
Should I add this one?

134
00:10:39,410 --> 00:10:43,610
Yeah. It captures Sayaka's charm.

135
00:10:54,310 --> 00:10:57,060
Oh, do the photos stop here?

136
00:10:57,060 --> 00:11:00,810
No, the rest are in the next album.

137
00:11:15,650 --> 00:11:17,780
[Sayaka Wakamatsu]

138
00:11:18,660 --> 00:11:20,230
<i>This uniform...</i>

139
00:11:20,230 --> 00:11:21,530
[Unhappiest wishes to you, Red Riding Hood]

140
00:11:23,950 --> 00:11:27,120
<i>So that was her middle school uniform.</i>

141
00:11:27,120 --> 00:11:31,980
<i>Does this mean Sayaka's mother
sent the threat?</i>

142
00:11:33,070 --> 00:11:37,100
Oh, Sayaka. What to do with a girl like her?

143
00:11:37,100 --> 00:11:39,610
She practically attracts trouble.

144
00:11:39,610 --> 00:11:42,340
Trouble?

145
00:11:43,040 --> 00:11:45,840
Not serious trouble, of course.

146
00:11:46,700 --> 00:11:52,230
She simply has a real habit
of bothering others.

147
00:11:52,230 --> 00:11:55,220
As her mother, I'm ashamed of her.

148
00:11:56,210 --> 00:12:00,630
How could she grow to be such a weak girl?

149
00:12:00,630 --> 00:12:02,840
What an absolute pity.

150
00:12:02,840 --> 00:12:07,570
She only continued to act depressed
in high school.

151
00:12:07,570 --> 00:12:12,220
Chie and Airi were her only saving graces.

152
00:12:12,860 --> 00:12:17,200
Really, she was lucky
to have friends like them.

153
00:12:19,080 --> 00:12:24,240
Now these two girls
are splendid individuals.

154
00:12:25,550 --> 00:12:28,120
Sayaka is no different, Mother.

155
00:12:29,020 --> 00:12:33,120
Every day, I feel blessed to have met her.

156
00:12:34,230 --> 00:12:39,300
She's a sweet, modest girl.
A real rarity nowadays.

157
00:12:39,300 --> 00:12:41,990
And her cooking is especially delicious.

158
00:12:43,180 --> 00:12:47,850
No, no. Her cooking is nothing special.

159
00:12:47,850 --> 00:12:51,190
Sure, she may have attended
a culinary school.

160
00:12:51,190 --> 00:12:55,180
But she only learned to make meager desserts.

161
00:12:55,180 --> 00:13:00,550
I had my expectations
for her career as a pâtissier,

162
00:13:00,550 --> 00:13:04,550
but she ultimately worked
a cash register, no?

163
00:13:04,550 --> 00:13:09,560
Even then, she quit due to a bit of trouble.

164
00:13:09,560 --> 00:13:16,700
That girl has no resolve, I tell you.
She can't keep at anything for long.

165
00:13:16,700 --> 00:13:19,250
- Mother, please -
- My, I almost forgot!

166
00:13:19,250 --> 00:13:22,860
The neighbors gave me some pastries.

167
00:13:22,860 --> 00:13:26,670
Let me grab some to accompany our tea.

168
00:13:32,420 --> 00:13:35,160
How could she say that
about her own daughter?

169
00:13:35,160 --> 00:13:38,560
All she's done is humiliate Sayaka.

170
00:13:38,560 --> 00:13:42,680
It's a bit much,
even under the pretext of "acting humble".

171
00:13:42,680 --> 00:13:44,010
Yeah.

172
00:13:44,810 --> 00:13:50,270
That toxic mother doesn't love Sayaka.

173
00:13:51,650 --> 00:13:53,550
Now I'm sure of it.

174
00:13:55,930 --> 00:13:58,940
She's the one who hurt Sayaka.

175
00:14:00,280 --> 00:14:01,790
What are you doing?

176
00:14:01,790 --> 00:14:03,270
My, what happened?

177
00:14:03,270 --> 00:14:05,400
I'm sorry, I spilled a bit of my tea.

178
00:14:05,400 --> 00:14:08,010
You should wash that right away.

179
00:14:08,010 --> 00:14:09,880
I suppose so.

180
00:14:09,880 --> 00:14:12,450
I'll head to the restroom.

181
00:14:19,850 --> 00:14:21,410
Here you go.

182
00:14:21,940 --> 00:14:23,660
Thank you.

183
00:14:41,340 --> 00:14:42,660
Excuse me.

184
00:14:42,660 --> 00:14:43,650
Yes?

185
00:14:43,650 --> 00:14:47,200
These are wonderful albums.

186
00:14:47,200 --> 00:14:48,760
- Really?
- Yes.

187
00:14:48,760 --> 00:14:52,740
I can see your love for your daughter
reflected in them.

188
00:14:52,740 --> 00:14:55,750
Hayashida is a wonderful match for her.

189
00:14:55,750 --> 00:14:59,760
He cares greatly for Sayaka.

190
00:14:59,760 --> 00:15:04,800
Yes. He graduated from an excellent school,
and has a promising career.

191
00:15:04,800 --> 00:15:08,120
I'm truly glad my daughter -

192
00:15:10,940 --> 00:15:13,200
Kazuomi?

193
00:15:16,860 --> 00:15:19,850
Are these from Sayaka's recitals?

194
00:15:19,850 --> 00:15:24,220
Yes, they are.
She won her first when she was seven.

195
00:15:24,220 --> 00:15:26,850
I see. That's amazing.

196
00:15:26,850 --> 00:15:30,570
I've always loved the violin,
ever since I was a young girl.

197
00:15:30,570 --> 00:15:33,470
Like mother, like daughter, no?

198
00:15:49,700 --> 00:15:51,460
What are you doing?

199
00:15:57,610 --> 00:16:02,020
Kazuomi, tell me what's going on.

200
00:16:02,020 --> 00:16:02,990
Well...

201
00:16:02,990 --> 00:16:08,100
I thought you two were acting strange.

202
00:16:08,100 --> 00:16:13,800
He didn't need to join us here, did he?

203
00:16:14,610 --> 00:16:15,960
Mother, I...

204
00:16:15,960 --> 00:16:17,990
Why have you really come today?

205
00:16:26,330 --> 00:16:30,910
Mother. What sort of medication is that?

206
00:16:34,390 --> 00:16:37,540
Your psychiatrist prescribed them,
did they not?

207
00:16:38,780 --> 00:16:43,830
Yes. The whole affair at the wedding
affected me significantly.

208
00:16:43,830 --> 00:16:46,010
Then are those sleeping pills?

209
00:16:46,750 --> 00:16:49,930
Why do you want to know?

210
00:16:49,930 --> 00:16:53,100
The reason Sayaka collapsed...

211
00:16:54,440 --> 00:16:57,120
wasn't solely because of an ulcer.

212
00:16:57,120 --> 00:16:58,670
What?

213
00:16:58,670 --> 00:17:03,650
Someone drugged her.

214
00:17:04,500 --> 00:17:06,330
Drugged her?

215
00:17:06,920 --> 00:17:09,540
<i>Sayaka!</i>

216
00:17:09,540 --> 00:17:11,460
Kazuomi...

217
00:17:13,070 --> 00:17:17,630
Are you suspecting I did such a thing?

218
00:17:17,630 --> 00:17:19,100
We simply want to confirm -

219
00:17:19,100 --> 00:17:22,230
I would never.
This is a psychotropic medication.

220
00:17:22,230 --> 00:17:23,730
Then please, show us the contents.

221
00:17:23,730 --> 00:17:25,530
Enough!

222
00:17:28,140 --> 00:17:33,610
You think I hurt Sayaka?

223
00:17:34,980 --> 00:17:38,420
The absolute disrespect.

224
00:17:40,260 --> 00:17:43,540
Do not even jest.

225
00:17:43,540 --> 00:17:50,310
You two could never understand how I felt
raising my child.

226
00:17:50,310 --> 00:17:58,570
I have lived my very life for Sayaka's sake.

227
00:17:59,330 --> 00:18:03,870
I have sacrificed everything
for her happiness.

228
00:18:03,870 --> 00:18:07,020
I'd be there for her. I'd worry for her.

229
00:18:07,020 --> 00:18:10,340
I gave up many things for her.

230
00:18:10,340 --> 00:18:17,140
And yet that child has betrayed
my every expectation.

231
00:18:20,880 --> 00:18:27,360
Even so, I love my daughter
from the bottom of my heart.

232
00:18:28,110 --> 00:18:34,060
I would never harm my own child.

233
00:18:37,020 --> 00:18:38,610
Mother...

234
00:18:47,220 --> 00:18:49,300
Just, wow.

235
00:18:54,550 --> 00:18:55,960
Excuse me?

236
00:19:01,160 --> 00:19:02,960
"Wow"?

237
00:19:04,910 --> 00:19:07,170
"Wow", you say?

238
00:19:09,610 --> 00:19:12,440
I-It was a slip of the tongue.

239
00:19:13,710 --> 00:19:16,070
I'm terribly sorry.

240
00:19:16,070 --> 00:19:20,750
You come to my home,
and meddle in my family's business?

241
00:19:20,750 --> 00:19:26,700
Who taught you manners?
Did you even attend school?

242
00:19:28,770 --> 00:19:30,720
Answer me.

243
00:19:31,780 --> 00:19:34,840
Are you a mere high school graduate?

244
00:19:36,300 --> 00:19:40,800
You must have attended a no-name school.

245
00:19:41,960 --> 00:19:46,620
I suppose that's no surprise,
given you're only a photographer.

246
00:19:47,610 --> 00:19:53,200
And now you've come here,
judging me for my own choices?

247
00:19:54,690 --> 00:19:57,480
Oh how I'd love to see your parents.

248
00:19:59,310 --> 00:20:03,780
They must not be very cultured themselves.

249
00:20:10,940 --> 00:20:16,000
Mother. Sakuraba is a skilled photographer.

250
00:20:17,620 --> 00:20:23,050
His work impressed you too, did they not?

251
00:20:24,490 --> 00:20:27,530
Forgive me for speaking out of turn,

252
00:20:27,530 --> 00:20:33,100
but you cannot judge a person
based on their education or career.

253
00:20:34,870 --> 00:20:37,320
Sakuraba's photos are first class.

254
00:20:37,320 --> 00:20:40,790
I will not allow you
to speak down on his work.

255
00:20:40,790 --> 00:20:42,820
His education doesn't matter.

256
00:20:42,820 --> 00:20:45,240
I trust him.

257
00:20:46,900 --> 00:20:50,080
I'm the one who asked for his help.

258
00:20:50,080 --> 00:20:56,250
He feels responsible, as another party
who was at the scene of the incident.

259
00:20:57,630 --> 00:21:04,270
And please, do not berate Sayaka as well.

260
00:21:05,280 --> 00:21:06,460
What?

261
00:21:06,460 --> 00:21:12,560
Mother, you held ill will towards Sayaka
for betraying your expectations.

262
00:21:14,470 --> 00:21:20,340
You couldn't stand to see her get married,
and escape from your clutches.

263
